r = \sin t + \cos t
r^2 = r\sin t+r\cos t 
x^2+y^2 = x + y
x^2+y^2 = x + y \iff x^2 - x + y^2 - y =0 
\left(x^2 - x + \frac 14\right) + \left(y^2 - y + \frac 14\right) = \frac 12
\left(x - \frac 12\right)^2 + \left(y - \frac 12\right)^2 = \left(\sqrt{\frac 12}\right)^2
\left(\frac 12, \frac 12\right)
\frac 1{\sqrt 2}
